import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.boxplot(x='budgetYear', y='value', data=data)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of values across budget years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Budget Years', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['forecastYear'])]
    data['forecastYear'] = data['forecastYear'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='forecastYear', y='value', hue='forecastYear', legend=True)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of values across forecast years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Forecast Year')
    plt.ylabel('Value')
    plt.legend(title='Forecast Year', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_grouped = data.groupby('budgetYear').mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='budgetYear', y='value', data=data_grouped)
    plt.title('What is the average value for each budget year?', wrap=True)
    chart.set(xlabel='Budget Year', ylabel='Average Value')
    plt.legend(title='Budget Year', loc='upper right', labels=data_grouped['budgetYear'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
